'''''-ina''''' is a [[Quenya]] suffix that has two meanings.<ref name=Eldarin>{{PE|Eldarin}}</ref>{{rp|68}}
==-ina<sup>1</sup>==
Used as an aorist suffix. This use is only mentioned in a marginal note and no examples are given.<ref name=Eldarin />{{rp|68}}
==-ina<sup>2</sup>==
Used as an adjectival suffix.
==Examples==
* ''cal'''ina''''' = lit. 'illuminated' "sunny, light" (''[[cala]]'', [[KAL]] light)<ref name=Eldarin />{{rp|153}}
* ''lamb'''ina''''' = "of tongue, spoken with tongue" (''[[lambe]]'' = "tongue")<ref name=Eldarin />{{rp|46}}<ref name=Eldarin />{{rp|123}}
* ''lat'''ina''''' = "used of freedom of movement, of things not encumbered with obstacles" ([[LAT]] open, unenclosed, free to entry)<ref name=Eldarin />{{rp|159}}
* ''ler'''ina''''' = "not guarded, reserved, made fast or owned" ([[LER]] free (of moveable or moving things), able to move as willed, unimpeded, unharmed, loose, not fixed fast or static)<ref name=Eldarin />{{rp|160}}
* ''ra'''ina''''' = "smiling, gracious, sweet faced" ([[RAYA]] smile, show pleasure or favour in facial expression)<ref name=Eldarin />{{rp|182}}
* ''[[Elerrína|Elerr'''ína''']]'' = "Crowned of Stars"<ref>{{S|Days}}</ref>
